This goes to fill in just a little bit of time,  as we get up and try to 
find  somewhere more congenial..  A series of pointless wonderings takes 
us to the MacDonalds on the upper levels of the station,  where a fit of 
group indecision and fear of the breakfast results in no-one going  in.. 
Outside,  a  weak  and watery sunrise is taking place,  lighting up  the 
grimy station interior.. Still as cold as ever.. Like the Grand old Duke 
of York's men,  we march back down again to breath in more diesel fumes, 
until  at long,  long last,  we size up and enter a cafe that we spotted 
earlier..

The cafe is almost open,  as we enter and demand coffees all round..  No 
sign of any food,  but the caffeine content once more is such, that mere 
nutrition  has  to  stand aside and concede  defeat..  Lightheaded  with 
relief,  we  fail to spot the next 'problem' that creeps up on us almost 
